Using the following PowerShell test, clients on this server *do* have the ability to access the MSSQL databases:

```powsh
 function Test-SQLConnection
{    
    [OutputType([bool])]
    Param
    (
        [Parameter(Mandatory=$true,
                    ValueFromPipelineByPropertyName=$true,
                    Position=0)]
        $ConnectionString
    )
    try
    {
        $sqlConnection = New-Object System.Data.SqlClient.SqlConnection $ConnectionString;
        $sqlConnection.Open();
        $sqlConnection.Close();

        return $true;
    }
    catch
    {
        return $false;
    }
} 

PS C:\windows\system32> Test-SQLConnection "Data Source=cisdr209w.princeton.edu;Initial Catalog=elements;Integrated Security=False;User ID=[...]"
True
PS C:\windows\system32> Test-SQLConnection "Data Source=foo.princeton.edu;Initial Catalog=bar[...]"
False 
```
